727614f-a.title: Queens: Northern Boulevard - 114th Street
727614f-a.text:
Northern Boulevard, east from near 1144th Street, across
Grand Central Parkway. The Boulevard was later widened when
the World's Fair of 1939-40 was erected in this area. On the
horizon is the village of Flushing.
P. L. Sperr  View 1: October 4, 1935
NO REPRODUCTIONS  View 21 May 20, 1936
